<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="798" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14224.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Extracts.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 17, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Last night the Convention formally deposed the Provisional President and
                            itself assumed the Government. The President of the Convention was named
                            the Executive of the Convention.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>